<refnamediv>
<refname>npm-help</refname>
<refpurpose>Get help on npm</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
<cmdsynopsis>
  <command>npm</command>    <arg choice='plain'><replaceable>help</replaceable></arg>
    <arg choice='plain'><replaceable>&lt;term&gt;</replaceable></arg>
    <arg choice='opt'><replaceable>&lt;terms..&gt;</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>If supplied a topic, then show the appropriate documentation page.</para>

<para>If the topic does not exist, or if multiple terms are provided, then run
the <emphasis remap='B'>help-search</emphasis> command to find a match.  Note that, if <emphasis remap='B'>help-search</emphasis>
finds a single subject, then it will run <emphasis remap='B'>help</emphasis> on that topic, so unique
matches are equivalent to specifying a topic name.</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id='configuration'><title>CONFIGURATION</title>

<refsect2 id='viewer'><title>viewer</title>
  <blockquote remap='RS'>
  <itemizedlist remap='IP+bullet'>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Default: "man" on Posix, "browser" on Windows</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Type: path</para>

    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  </blockquote> <!-- remap='RE' -->

<para>The program to use to view help content.</para>

<para>Set to <emphasis remap='B'>"browser"</emphasis> to view html help content in the default web browser.</para>
</refsect2>
</refsect1>

